CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier, November 5, 1955, pg. 1B reads: "Dr. Azikiwe, publisher of five newspapers, enjoys chance to put Courier press to test. "This is how you do it," he tells Production manager Wilkins and Head Pressman Waters."
TitMainTitle: Eastern Nigerian Prime Minister Nnamdi Azikiwe, standing with two unknown men in Pittsburgh Courier Newspaper printing plant
